      },
      "source": [
        "### data Extraction with Pandas"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "KcMQfu8trrSN"
      },
      "source": [
        "selecting data by loc(),iloc()                 slicing also allowed"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "Ml0cbPiRrzbK"
      },
      "source": [
        "loc() is label-based, so we have to specify rows and columns baseed on therir index/row and columns lables"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "8yrhMBJ2tzp0"
      },
      "source": [
        "in loc()  valne = df.loc['zero']   list = df.;oc['zero', 'two']       slicing  = df.loc['zero' : 'two']  in slicing \"zero\" and 'two' are included"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "SE8Nx1bYsUUV"
      },
      "source": [
        "iloc() is integer position-based, so we have to specify rows and columns by theri integar position values (0-based integer position)      it all wayes start with 0 index"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "QvtjLCqYtvjc"
      },
      "source": [
        "in iloc()  valne = df.loc[0]   list = df.;oc[0,2]       slicing  = df.loc[0 : 2]  in slicing 0 included and 2 in exclued like normal slicing"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "LZyegbH7vntl"
